    <!-- Item 6 -->
    <div class="panel panel-default">
      <div onclick="return toggleDisplay(this)" class="panel-heading" role="tab" id="faq-2-h-6">
        <h4 class="panel-title">
          <span>
            {{ 'FAQ2.WHAT_IS_THE_MAX_AMOUNT_OF_NETWORK_CONNECTIONS' | i18n }}
          </span>
        </h4>
        <div class="panel-body">
          <p>
            The outbound connection is cap at <span>16 max</span>.<br />
            If you want more connections, you need to accept inbound connections. <br />
            The wallet listen on port 15714. Just check if that port is not blocked. Also, It takes time for other
            peers to discover your nodes and connect to it.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div><!-- / .panel -->

    <!-- Item 7 -->
    <div class="panel panel-default">
      <div onclick="return toggleDisplay(this)" class="panel-heading" role="tab" id="faq-2-h-7">
        <h4 class="panel-title">
          <span>
            {{ 'FAQ2.UPGRADING_WALLET' | i18n }}
          </span>
        </h4>
        <div class="panel-body">
          <p>
            Just <span>replace the old binary with the new one</span>. <br />
            Before upgrading, make sure that you have the lastest <span>backup of your
            wallet.dat file</span>.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div><!-- / .panel -->

    <!-- Item 8 -->
    <div class="panel panel-default">
      <div onclick="return toggleDisplay(this)" class="panel-heading" role="tab" id="faq-2-h-8">
        <h4 class="panel-title">
          <span>
            {{ 'FAQ2.CHANGING_WALLET_LOCATION' | i18n }}
          </span>
        </h4>
        <div class="panel-body">
          <p>
            Create a <span>shortcut that runs blackcoin-qt.exe -datadir=NEW LOCATION</span>
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div><!-- / .panel -->

    <!-- Item 9 -->
    <div class="panel panel-default">
      <div onclick="return toggleDisplay(this)" class="panel-heading" role="tab" id="faq-2-h-9">
        <h4 class="panel-title">
          <span>
            {{ 'FAQ2.HOW_OFTEN_DO_I_NEED_TO_BACKUP_MY_WALLET' | i18n }}
          </span>
        </h4>
        <div class="panel-body">
          <p>
            <span>If you send coins from the wallet to other addresses</span>, then you
            should back it up, since sending can create a new change addresses. <br />
            If you are not doing anything other than staking and receiving coins to the same address, then you
            probably don't need to create additional backups.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div><!-- / .panel -->

    <!-- Item 10 -->
    <div class="panel panel-default">
      <div onclick="return toggleDisplay(this)" class="panel-heading" role="tab" id="faq-2-h-10">
        <h4 class="panel-title">
          <span>
            {{ 'FAQ2.HOW_TO_STOP_STAKING_TO_BE_ABLE_TO_SEND_COINS' | i18n }}
          </span>
        </h4>
        <div class="panel-body">
          <p>
            Your balance which is <span>staking will be freed after 501 confirmations</span>. <br />
            You can track progress in the Transactions tab.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div><!-- / .panel -->

    <!-- Item 11 -->
    <div class="panel panel-default">
      <div onclick="return toggleDisplay(this)" class="panel-heading" role="tab" id="faq-2-h-11">
        <h4 class="panel-title">
          <span>
            {{ 'FAQ2.SENDING_BLACKCOINS_FROM_CERTAIN_ADDRESS' | i18n }}
          </span>
        </h4>
        <div class="panel-body">
          <p>
            If you <span>generated few addresses in your wallet</span>, but you would like
            to <span>choose certain one</span> to send BlackCoins from: <br />
            Settings >> options >> display >> "check" display coin control features(experts only) >> apply;<br />
            Send >> inputs >> "check" the address you would like to send from. <br />
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div><!-- / .panel -->

